 4Â° Biodiversity is the variability of the living organisms of all types including man, animals of all species, plants of all types, be it on land or underground, in water as      well as in the atmosphere and the interactions among them. Biodiversity means all       things that breath.
	* Ecosystem is a particular place on land or in water where biodiversity is found                and complement each other;
	* A biotope is a geographical area where all the environment's physical and       chemical factors remain more or less constant;
	* Ecology is a study of the different kinds of environment where biodiversity live,       reproduce and die, as well as the relationship among them.

